// Cryptol spec: identity-on-discriminant for an AuthResult enum.
//
// The implementation switches over `enum class AuthResult : uint8_t`
// with three valid tags (0, 1, 2) and ends with __builtin_unreachable()
// (or `unreachable_unchecked` in Rust) so any other discriminant is
// undefined behaviour at the source level.
//
// SAW models the LLVM `unreachable` instruction as a verification
// failure when reached. Without a type-derived `r <= 2` precondition,
// the solver picks `r = 0xff` (or any value outside the enum range),
// the switch falls through to the unreachable, and verification
// DISPROVES with a counterexample SAW believes is impossible.
//
// The whole point of beads `saw-spec-gen-xip` is to make saw-spec-gen
// emit that precondition automatically from the EnumDecl / mir-json
// ADT info so this case VERIFIES.

classify_spec : [8] -> [32]
classify_spec r = zext r
